<subSubSection lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1517,2010]" lastBlockId="54.[151,1436,151,284]" lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1841,1865]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1900" box="[330,495,1841,1865]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindensis">
<emphasis box="[330,495,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Uca sindensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcock, A." box="[923,1094,1841,1865]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="279 - 456" refId="ref44374" refString="Alcock, A. (1900) Material for a carcinological Fauna of India. No. 6: The Brachyura Catometopa, or Grapsoidea. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 69 (2), 279 - 456." type="journal article" year="1900">Alcock (1900)</bibRefCitation>
from Karachi (
<collectingCountry box="[1291,1389,1841,1865]" name="Pakistan" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
) as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1900" box="[151,527,1877,1901]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Gelasimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="inversus" variety="sindensis">
<emphasis box="[151,369,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Gelasimus inversus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[424,527,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">sindensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Crane (1975) assigned this species to her new subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Crane, 1975" authorityName="Crane" authorityYear="1975" box="[1172,1432,1877,1901]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Amphiuca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1172,1285,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Amphiuca</emphasis>
Crane, 1975
</taxonomicName>
. Beinlich &amp; von Hagen (2006) included it with other Indo-West Pacific wide-front fiddler crabs in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bott" authorityYear="1973" box="[151,290,1949,1973]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Paraleptuca">
<emphasis box="[151,290,1949,1973]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Paraleptuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They stated that this subgenus is heterogeneous, a statement which was supported by Naderloo 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,1949,1973]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">et al</emphasis>
. (2010). The taxonomic position of the species within the large genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach, 1814 [in Leach, 1813-" authorityYear="1815" box="[920,967,1986,2009]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[920,967,1986,2009]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Uca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not clear, and need detailed genetic and morphological work in order to establish the exact systematic position, which is being done in an ongoing study by Naderloo &amp; Türkay (in preparation). 
<bibRefCitation author="Collins, M. J. &amp; Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A." box="[629,891,188,212]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="318 - 328" refId="ref46387" refString="Collins, M. J., Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A. (1984) Redescription of Uca sindensis (Alcock, 1900) (Brachyura: Ocypodidae) with notes on the ecology of a population from Kuwait. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 4 (2), 318 - 328, figs. 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1984">
Collins 
<emphasis box="[729,791,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al</emphasis>
. (1984)
</bibRefCitation>
redescribed this species providing detailed morphological and biological accounts of it from 
<collectingCountry box="[711,797,223,247]" name="Kuwait" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
. More biological aspects of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1900" box="[1116,1253,224,248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindensis">
<emphasis box="[1116,1136,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1150,1253,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">sindensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mokhlesi, A. &amp; Kamrani, E. &amp; Backwell, P. &amp; Sajjadi, M." box="[151,403,260,284]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="245 - 249" refId="ref49943" refString="Mokhlesi, A., Kamrani, E., Backwell, P. &amp; Sajjadi, M. (2011) Study on the behavior of two fiddler crabs, Uca sindensis and Uca annulipes (Decapoda: Ocypodidae), in Bandar Abbas, Iran. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the Unated Kingdom, 91 (1), 245 - 249." type="journal article" year="2011">
Mokhlesi 
<emphasis box="[263,312,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
